==English==
===Verb===
'''[[take]] a [[back]] [[seat]]'''
#{{idiom}} To be second to someone or something; to be less important or have a lower [[priority]].
#: ''"But as with most kids, [[politics]] '''took a backseat to''' daily life."'' &mdash; [[w:My Life|My Life]] by [[w:Bill Clinton|Bill Clinton]]

